= Oregon Core -- Database information =

Copyright (C) Oregon Core (http://www.oregoncore.com)

Installation: (with OregonDB)
  1: sql/create_mysql.sql
  2: sql/world.sql
  3: sql/characters.sql
  4: sql/realmd.sql
  5: sql/oregon_database.zip (must be extracted first)
  6: sql/update/*.sql (apply all patches from the 3 subfolders (charaacters, realmd, world)
  
Installation: (without OregonDB) (no support from Oregon for DB Problems)
  1: sql/create_mysql.sql
  2: sql/world.sql
  3: sql/characters.sql
  4: sql/realmd.sql
  5: Install your own world DB (or use a different DB Project)
  6: sql/update/*.sql (apply all patches from the 3 subfolders (charaacters, realmd, world)

Update from existing Oregoncore Rev. (rev. before 1600)
  1: Start to apply all Patches from sql/old/database/ Folder starting at your revision until the last update is applyed
  2: Apply all updates from sql/old/updates/world/ sting from rev 1419
  3: Apply all necessary updates from sql/old/updates/characters/ and sql/old/updates/realmd/
  4: Continue reading the next block
  
Update from existing Oregoncore Rev. (rev. 1600+)
  1: You must only apply the updates from sql/updates/ folder to the correct Database.